description: Visually inspect the connections and cable pairs between the power supply module and control module 1 to check for miswiring, loose, or swapped cables that could prevent voltage delivery., outcome='All connections between the Power Supply Unit (PSU) and Control Module 1 are matched as follows: PSU Output Cable (+) is connected to Control Input Cable (+) 1, and PSU Output Cable (−) is connected to Control Input Cable (−) 1. No polarity inversion detected in the inspected connections. All cables appear to be physically mated to their corresponding polarity.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power Supply Module (remove from main circuit),
description: Completely disconnect the power supply module from the downstream control modules and test the voltage across its output cables (with a good battery inserted) to see if the PSU outputs 12V when no external load is present., outcome="Continuity for both PSU output cables (+) and (−) is nominal at 0.1 Ω. However, voltage measured at 'PSU Output Cable (+)' is 0.012 V and at 'PSU Output Cable (−)' is 0.0 V, which is significantly below the expected 12V output with no external load.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
